TABLE 1
. Comparison between specific characters of 

Dinahia

and similar genera. 
Char. 1
= maxillary palpomeres IV enlargeds in relation to maxillary palpomeres III; 
Char. 2
= maxillary palpomeres IV with straight apical margin; 
Char. 3
= antennomeres IX–X as long as wide or wider than long; 
Char. 4
= base of prosternal process not projected; 
Char. 5
= prosternal process with a keel; 
Char. 6
= metaventral process more prominent than mesoventral process; 
Char. 7
= tarsomere V without spiniform ventroapical projection; and 
Char. 8
= divergent claws. ✓ = Presence, ⨉ = Absence.
